Infrastructure Setup:
Set up a dedicated server infrastructure with sufficient storage capacity and computational resources to host your data lake.
Ensure reliable network connectivity between the servers and the client machines accessing the data lake.
Perforce Installation and Configuration:
Install Perforce server on a designated machine in your infrastructure.
Configure Perforce to create repositories and folders for organizing your data files.
Establish access controls and permissions to ensure proper data security and user management.
Bitbucket Installation and Configuration:
Install Bitbucket server on a separate machine in your infrastructure.
Configure Bitbucket repositories to store your codebase and enable version control.
Implement access controls and permissions to govern code collaboration and versioning.
Choose a NoSQL Database:
Evaluate various NoSQL databases suitable for your metadata management needs, such as MongoDB, Apache Cassandra, or Amazon DynamoDB.
Install and configure the selected NoSQL database on a separate server in your infrastructure.
Define the schema or structure of the metadata to be stored in the database.
API Development for Metadata Management:
Design and develop APIs to facilitate interaction between Perforce, Bitbucket, and the NoSQL database.
Create API endpoints for metadata retrieval, update, and search operations.
Implement logic to generate and store object hashes based on file content to identify file updates accurately.
Metadata Integration with Perforce and Bitbucket:
Establish integration between Perforce and the NoSQL database to capture and store metadata related to data files.
Develop triggers or hooks within Perforce to automatically update metadata in the NoSQL database when new files are added or existing files are modified.
Integrate Bitbucket with the NoSQL database to capture metadata related to code repositories and code changes.
Data Access and Querying:
Develop mechanisms to access and query the data files stored in Perforce using APIs or direct integrations.
Implement search functionalities in the NoSQL database to enable efficient querying of metadata.
Secure data access by implementing appropriate authentication and authorization mechanisms.
Data Governance and Security:
Establish data governance practices, including data lineage tracking, data quality checks, and data lifecycle management.
Enforce security measures such as data encryption, access controls, and auditing to protect data integrity and privacy.
Ensure compliance with relevant data protection regulations and industry standards.
Testing and Deployment:
Conduct thorough testing of the integrated solution, including metadata management, file updates, code versioning, and data access.
Perform performance and scalability testing to ensure the data lake can handle the expected data volumes and user loads.
Develop a deployment plan and roll out the solution to the production environment with proper backup and recovery mechanisms in place.
Ongoing Maintenance and Monitoring:
Monitor the performance, availability, and security of the data lake components.
Regularly update and patch software components to ensure the latest security fixes and feature enhancements.
Continuously optimize the system based on usage patterns and evolving requirements.
